 bearing witness to the possibilities and problems of human community and shared experience in the real world. A rich and engrossing book, What Is Pastoral? will soon take its place as the definitive study of pastoral literature. "Alpers succeeds brilliantly. . . . [He] offers . . . a wealth of new insight into the origins, development, and flowering of the pastoral."—Ann-Maria Contarino, Renaissance Quarterly  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aPastoral literaturexHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  apastoral, shepherds, herding, herd, livestock, idealization, idealized manner, representation, western literature, literary, rural themes, ruralism, nature, natural world, fiction, humble, humanity, human beings, nostalgia, criticism, lyricism, narration, speakers, genre, virgil, sarah orne jewett, william shakespeare, cervantes, robert frost, simplicity, country life.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package Archive 1990-1999z978311066785140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226015231423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226015231/original  a978-3-11-066785-1  University of Chicago Press eBook Package Archive 1990-1999c1990d1999  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles